        jDialog14.setTitle("Help");
        jDialog14.setResizable(false);
        jDialog14.setSize(new java.awt.Dimension(631, 370));

        jTextArea5.setEditable(false);
        jTextArea5.setColumns(20);
        jTextArea5.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Dialog", 0, 14)); // NOI18N
        jTextArea5.setRows(5);
        jTextArea5.setText("                                             ~ User Guide ~\n                                          --------------------------\n\n                                               - Introduction\nThis system classifies white fish fillets using image processing and a \nclustering method. When a fillet is detected the system captures three \nimages of the fillet using three different light sources. These images\nare filtered using image processing methods and the following data \nis extracted: The Area of the fillet and the Area of the bloodspots in each\nimage. This data is the evaluated with the cluster and the fillet is classified \nas either Good, Medium, Bad, or Small.\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                              - Startup\nFor running the system one can use a sensor connected to the arduino, or\nautomatic detection using the \"Fillet detection\" tool.\n\n1. Go to       Tools --> Fillet detection --> Yes\n   Autodetection will now display as on in the down left corner.\n\n2. Press the Start button to start the system.\n   You can pause the system by pressing the Stop button.\n\n3. Checking the \"Show contours\" checkbox enables visualisation\n    of the contours in the image.\n\n4. The section on the right will display data extracted from the fillet, \n    aswell as number of fillets checked during the runtime.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                                 ~ Tools ~\n                                          -----------------------\n\n                                           - Manual Controll\n 1. Manual controll lets you take individual images and choose light source.\n 2. The three images displayed are the original image, the segmented fillet,\n    and the segmented bloodspots.\n3. The down left section displays information regarding the fillet and the bloodspots.\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                                  - Logging\n1. Turning on logging writes the data from each fillet to a file along with the date\n    and time logging was started.\n2. This file can be used to retrain the classification algorithm if necesary.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                             - Fillet detection\n1. Fillet detection is a automatic method for capturing images when a fillet is \n    visable.\n2. The tool checks two boxes in the image, and when both boxes contains a certain \n     amount of white pixels, it detects this as a fillet.\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                              - Retrain cluster\n1. This tool lets you retrain the classification algorithm using ARFF files containing\n     the correct data and attributes.\n\n\n                                                      ~ View ~\n                                                 -------------------\n\n                                                - Videostream\n1. Videostream lets you view live video from the camera.\n2. By checking the \"Show boxes\" checkbox you can view the boxes used\n     in the fillet detection tool.\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                                 - View color images\n1. This window lets you view the three different images captured of each\n     fillet. One red, green, and blue iluminated image.\n2. By checking the \"Show segmented blood spots\" checkbox, you can see \n    the segmented bloodspots in each image.\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                                    - Total fillet count\n1. This window shows the total amount of fillets the system has classified aswell as\n     their classification.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n                                                             ~ Exit ~\n                                                        ------------------\n1. Lets you safely exit the application.\n");
        jScrollPane5.setViewportView(jTextArea5);

